      "title": "BOHM: Zero-Cost Hierarchical Attribution for Compound AI Systems",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.22866",
      "summary": "arXiv:2605.22866v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: Compound AI systems route tasks through hierarchies of specialised components. Attribution is dominated by Shapley-based methods (SHAP), which decompose a coalition value function into per-component marginal contributions and require evaluation of the system on arbitrary component subsets. That requirement fails for third-party APIs, opaque endpoints",
